President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring January 16, 2017, as the Martin Luther King, Jr., Federal Holiday. The proclamation highlights the importance of Dr. King's legacy and his impact on the Civil Rights Movement. It emphasizes the need for continued progress in areas such as economic opportunity, access to education, and equal treatment under the law. The proclamation encourages Americans to observe the day with civic, community, and service projects in honor of Dr. King. It also reminds people to visit the MLK Day of Service website to find service projects across the country. The proclamation concludes by urging individuals to embrace Dr. King's teachings of unconditional love and understanding, and to work towards a more just and equal society.